briefdescription.para: The #SDCardDriver_Deinit API is used to deinitialize the SD card module.

simplesect.para: In case of any other error refer #BSP_SDCard_SetCSHigh, #BSP_SDCard_Disable, #BSP_SDCard_Disconnect or #MCU_SPI_Deinitialize error codes.

briefdescription.para: The SDCardDriver_DiskInitialize API is used to initialize SD-card Disk sector. The initialization does the following: (1) verify the type of disk and card or disk status. (2) Enables the clock for SD card communication. (3) validating the Disk by passing commands and expected the responds.
The SDCardDriver_DiskIoctl API is used to have the functionalities to get sector count, sector size, block size. It also used to invalidate the disk initialization.

parameterdescription.para: Physical drive number (0)- Supports only single drive
Control code to specify the functionality

simplesect.para: SDCARD_DISK_NOT_READY SD card is Not Ready.
SDCARD_RW_FAIL SD card read write failed.
In case of any other error refer #BSP_SDCard_SetCSHigh or #BSP_SDCard_SetCSLow error codes.

briefdescription.para: The SDCardDriver_GetDetectStatus API is used to get the status of the SD card whether the SD card has been inserted or removed.

simplesect.para: SDCARD_NOT_INSERTED - SD card is not present.

briefdescription.para: The SDCardDriver_GetDiskStatus API is used to get the disk initialization status.

The #SDCardDriver_Init API is used to initialize the SD card module. The initialization does the following: (1) SD Card related Port, Pin, mode and dout settings. (2) Enables the clock. (3) Registers the call back function which will be triggered when card inserted or removed. (4) SPI initialization with SD card related parameters.

simplesect.para: In case of any other error refer #MCU_SPI_Initialize or #BSP_SDCard_Enable error codes.
